quran[564]{c,v,t}:
  78,1,ABOUT WHAT are they asking
  78,2,About the fateful tidings ―
  78,3,the theme of their disputes
  78,4,But they shall learn
  78,5,then they shall surely learn
  78,6,Did We not spread the earth like a bed
  78,7,and raise the mountains like supporting pillars
  78,8,We created you in pairs
  78,9,and gave you rest in sleep
  78,10,We made the night a mantle
  78,11,and ordained the day for work
  78,12,We built above you seven mighty heavens
  78,13,and placed in them a glowing lamp
  78,14,We sent down abundant water from the clouds
  78,15,to bringing forth grain and varied plants
  78,16,and gardens thick with foliage
  78,17,Fixed is the Day of Judgement
  78,18,"On that day the Trumpet shall be blown, and you shall come in multitudes"
  78,19,The gates of heaven shall swing Open
  78,20,and the mountains shall pass away into a mirage
  78,21,Hell will lie in ambush
  78,22,a home for the transgressors
  78,23,Therein shall they abide long ages
  78,24,therein they shall taste neither refreshment nor any drink
  78,25,save scalding water and decaying filth
  78,26,a fitting recompense
  78,27,They never expected a reckoning
  78,28,and roundly denied Our revelations
  78,29,But We kept account of what they did and wrote it down
  78,30,"So taste this: for We shall give you nothing but mounting torment!‘"
  78,31,"As for the righteous, there shall surely be a triumph"
  78,32,gardens and vineyards
  78,33,and tender-bosomed maidens for companions
  78,34,a truly overflowing cup
  78,35,"Therein shall they hear no idle talk, nor any falsehood"
  78,36,Such is the recompense of your Lord ― a gift that will suffice them
  78,37,"the Lord of the heavens and the earth and all that lies between them; the Merciful, from whom they have no power to speak"
  78,38,"On the day when the Spirit and the angels stand up in their ranks, they shall not speak; except him who shall receive the sanction of the Merciful and declare what is right"
  78,39,"That day is sure to come. Let him who will, seek a way back to his Lord"
  78,40,"We have forewarned you of an imminent scourge: The day when man will look upon his works and the unbeliever say: ‘Would that I were dust!‘"
  79,1,BY THOSE who snatch away men‘s souls
  79,2,and those who gently release them
  79,3,by those who float at will
  79,4,and those who speed headlong
  79,5,by those who govern the affairs of this world
  79,6,On the day the Trumpet sounds
  79,7,its first and second blast
  79,8,hearts shall on that day be filled with terror
  79,9,and eyes shall stare with awe
  79,10,"They say: ‘When we are turned to hollow bones, shall we be restored to life?‘"
  79,11,Even if we should be decayed bones
  79,12,"And they say: ‘So it is a fruitless transformation!‘"
  79,13,But with one blast
  79,14,they shall return to the earth‘s surface
  79,15,Have you heard the story of Moses
  79,16,"His Lord called out to him in the sacred valley of Ţuwā, saying"
  79,17,"Go to Pharaoh: he has transgressed all bounds"
  79,18,"and say: \"Will you reform yourself"
  79,19,"I will guide you to your Lord, that you may have fear of Him.‘"
  79,20,He showed Pharaoh the mightiest sign
  79,21,but he denied it and rebelled
  79,22,He quickly went away and
  79,23,"summoning all his men, made to them a proclamation"
  79,24,‘I am your supreme Lord.‘ he said
  79,25,"So God smote him with the scourge of the life to come, and of this life"
  79,26,Surely in this there is a lesson for the God-fearing
  79,27,Are you harder to create or the heaven He has built
  79,28,He raised it high and fashioned it
  79,29,giving darkness to its night and brightness to its day
  79,30,After that He spread the earth
  79,31,"and, drawing water from its depth, brought forth its pastures"
  79,32,He set down the mountains
  79,33,for you and for your cattle to delight in
  79,34,But when the supreme calamity strikes ―
  79,35,the day when man will call to mind his labours ―
  79,36,when Hell appears to those with eyes to see ―
  79,37,he that transgressed
  79,38,and chose this present life
  79,39,shall have his home in Hell
  79,40,and he that feared to stand before his Lord
  79,41,and curbed his soul‘s desire shall have his home in Paradise
  79,42,They question you about the Hour. ‘When will it come?‘
  79,43,But how are you to know
  79,44,Only your Lord knows when the end will come
  79,45,Your duty is but to warn those that fear it
  79,46,"On the day they see it, it will seem as if they had lingered but one evening, or one morning"
  80,1,HE¹ FROWNED and turned his back
  80,2,when the blind man came towards him
  80,3,How could you¹ tell? He might have sought to purify himself
  80,4,"He might have remembered, and remembrance might have done him good"
  80,5,But to the wealthy man
  80,6,you were all attention
  80,7,although the fault would not be yours if he remained uncleansed
  80,8,Yet to him that came to you with zeal
  80,9,and awe
  80,10,you paid no heed
  80,11,No! This is an Admonition
  80,12,"let him who will, bear it in mind"
  80,13,It is set down on honoured pages
  80,14,exalted and purified
  80,15,by the hands of devout and gracious scribes
  80,16,Noble and dutiful
  80,17,Let man perish! How ungrateful he is
  80,18,From what did He create him
  80,19,From a little germ He created him and gave him due proportion
  80,20,He made his path smooth for him
  80,21,then caused him to die and stowed him in a grave
  80,22,He will surely bring him back to life when He pleases
  80,23,Yet he declines to do His bidding
  80,24,Let man reflect on the food he eats
  80,25,how We pour down the rain in torrents
  80,26,and cleave the earth asunder
  80,27,how We bring forth the corn
  80,28,the grapes and the fresh vegetation
  80,29,the olive and the palm
  80,30,the thickets
  80,31,the fruit-trees and the green pasture
  80,32,for you and for your cattle to delight in
  80,33,But when the dread blast is sounded
  80,34,on that day each man will forsake his brother
  80,35,his mother and his father
  80,36,his consort and his children
  80,37,for each one of them will on that day have enough sorrow of his own
  80,38,On that day there shall be beaming faces
  80,39,laughing and joyful
  80,40,On that day there shall be faces covered with dust
  80,41,veiled with darkness
  80,42,These shall be the faces of the degenerate blasphemers
  81,1,WHEN THE sun ceases to shine
  81,2,when the stars fall
  81,3,and the mountains are blown away
  81,4,when camels big with young are left untended
  81,5,and the wild beasts are together herded
  81,6,when the seas are set ablaze
  81,7,and souls are reunited
  81,8,"when the infant girl,¹ buried alive, is asked"
  81,9,for what crime she was slain
  81,10,when the records of men‘s deeds are laid open
  81,11,and heaven is stripped bare
  81,12,when Hell turns into a Conflagration
  81,13,and Paradise is brought near
  81,14,then each soul shall learn what it has done
  81,15,I swear by the turning planets
  81,16,and by the stars that rise and set
  81,17,"by the night, when it darkens"
  81,18,and the first breath of morning
  81,19,this is the Word of a messenger gracious and mighty
  81,20,held in honour by the Lord of the Throne
  81,21,"obeyed, and faithful to his trust"
  81,22,"No, your countryman² is not possessed"
  81,23,He saw him³ on the clear horizon
  81,24,He does not grudge the secrets of the unseen
  81,25,nor is this the utterance of an accursed demon
  81,26,Whither then are you going
  81,27,This is but an Admonition to all mankind
  81,28,to those among you that have the will to be upright
  81,29,"Yet you cannot will, except by the will of God, Lord of the Universe"
  82,1,WHEN THE sky is rent asunder
  82,2,when the stars scatter
  82,3,and the oceans surge together
  82,4,when the graves are hurled about
  82,5,each soul shall know what it has done and what it has failed to do
  82,6,O man! What evil has enticed you from your gracious Lord
  82,7,"who created you, and gave you due proportions and an upright form"
  82,8,In whatever shape He willed He could have moulded you
  82,9,No! But you deny the Last Judgement
  82,10,Surely there are guardians watching over you
  82,11,noble recorders
  82,12,who know of what you do
  82,13,The righteous will surely be in bliss
  82,14,And the wicked shall be in Hell
  82,15,burning therein upon the Judgement-day
  82,16,nor shall they ever escape from it
  82,17,Would that you knew what the Day of Judgement is
  82,18,"Again, would that you knew what the Day of Judgement is"
  82,19,It is the day when no soul shall have the power to help another soul and God will reign supreme
  83,1,WOE BETIDE the unjust
  83,2,"who, when people measure for them, exact in full"
  83,3,"but when they measure or weigh for them, defraud them"
  83,4,Do they not think they will be raised to life
  83,5,upon a fateful day
  83,6,the day when mankind will stand before the Lord of the Universe
  83,7,No! The record of the sinners is in Sijjīn
  83,8,Would that you knew what Sijjīn is
  83,9,It is a sealed book
  83,10,On that day woe betide the disbelievers
  83,11,who deny the Last Judgement
  83,12,None denies it except the sinful transgressor
  83,13,"who, when Our revelations are recited to him, says: ‘Fables of the ancients!‘"
  83,14,No! But their own deeds have drawn a veil over their hearts
  83,15,No! On a screen shall on that day be set between them and their Lord
  83,16,Then shall they burn in Hell
  83,17,"and shall be told: ‘This is what you denied!‘"
  83,18,No! But the record of the righteous shall be in ‘Illiyyūn
  83,19,Would that you knew what ‘Illiyyūn is
  83,20,It is a sealed book
  83,21,seen only by the favoured ones
  83,22,The righteous will surely be in bliss
  83,23,Reclining upon soft couches they will gaze around
  83,24,and in their faces you shall mark the glow of joy
  83,25,They shall be served with pure nectar to drink
  83,26,"securely sealed, whose very dregs are musk: for this let all contenders emulously strive"
  83,27,tempered with the waters of Tasnīm
  83,28,a spring at which the favoured will refresh themselves
  83,29,Those who transgress laugh at the faithful
  83,30,and wink at one another as they pass by them
  83,31,When they meet their own kin they speak of them with jests
  83,32,"and when they see them say: ‘These have surely lost their way.‘"
  83,33,Yet they were not sent to be their keepers
  83,34,But on that day the faithful will at the infidels laugh
  83,35,as they recline upon their couches and gaze around
  83,36,Shall not the infidels be rewarded according to what they did
  84,1,WHEN THE sky is rent apart
  84,2,obeying her Lord in true submission
  84,3,when the earth expands
  84,4,and casts out all that is within her and becomes empty
  84,5,obeying her Lord in true submission; then
  84,6,"O man, who labour constantly to meet your Lord, shall you meet Him"
  84,7,He that is given his book in his right hand
  84,8,shall have a lenient reckoning
  84,9,and shall go back rejoicing to his people
  84,10,But he that is given his book behind his back
  84,11,shall call down destruction on himself
  84,12,and burn in the Conflagration
  84,13,for he lived rejoicing among his people
  84,14,and thought he would never turn back
  84,15,Yes; but his Lord was ever watching him
  84,16,I swear by the glow of sunset
  84,17,"by the night, and all that it envelops"
  84,18,"by the moon, in her full perfection"
  84,19,that you shall march onwards from stage to stage
  84,20,Why then do they not believe
  84,21,or kneel down in prayer when the Koran is read to them
  84,22,The unbelievers indeed are in denial
  84,23,but God knows best the falsehoods they believe in
  84,24,Therefore proclaim to them a woeful scourge
  84,25,save those who believe and do good works; for theirs is an unfailing recompense
  85,1,BY THE heaven with its constellations
  85,2,By the Promised Day
  85,3,"By the Witness, and that which is witnessed"
  85,4,Cursed¹ be the diggers of the trench
  85,5,with its consuming fire
  85,6,as they sat around it
  85,7,to witness what they did to the faithful
  85,8,"Nor did they avenge themselves on them for aught but that they believed in God, the Almighty, the Praised One"
  85,9,who has sovereignty over the heavens and the earth. And God is the Witness of all things
  85,10,"Those that persecute believers, men or women, and never repent shall have the torment of Hell, the torment of the blazing fire"
  85,11,But those that believe and do good works shall have Gardens watered by running brooks. That is the supreme triumph
  85,12,Stern indeed is the vengeance of your Lord
  85,13,He it is who brings into being and then restores to life
  85,14,Forgiving and loving
  85,15,He is the Lord of the Glorious Throne
  85,16,the Executor of His own will
  85,17,Have you not heard the story of the warriors
  85,18,of Pharaoh and of Thamūd
  85,19,Yet the unbelievers are still in denial
  85,20,God surrounds them from behind
  85,21,Surely this is a glorious Koran
  85,22,on a tablet preserved
  86,1,"BY THE heaven, and by the nightly visitant"
  86,2,Would that you knew what the nightly visitant is
  86,3,It is the star of piercing brightness
  86,4,For every soul there is a guardian
  86,5,Let man reflect from what he is created
  86,6,he was created from an ejaculated fluid
  86,7,that issues from between the loins and the ribs
  86,8,Surely He has power to bring him back
  86,9,on the day when consciences are searched
  86,10,"Helpless shall he be, with none to succour him"
  86,11,By the heaven with its recurring cycles
  86,12,"and by the earth, ever bursting with new growth"
  86,13,this¹ is a discerning utterance
  86,14,no flippant jest
  86,15,They scheme and scheme
  86,16,"and I, too, scheme and scheme"
  86,17,"Therefore bear with the unbelievers, and let them be awhile"
  87,1,"PRAISE THE Name of your Lord, the Most High"
  87,2,who created all things and gave them due proportion
  87,3,who has ordained their destinies and guided them
  87,4,who brings forth the green pasture
  87,5,then turns it to withered grass
  87,6,"We shall make you read, so that you shall never forget"
  87,7,"except as God pleases. He has knowledge of the manifest, and the hidden"
  87,8,We shall guide you to the smoothest path
  87,9,"Therefore admonish, if admonishment will avail"
  87,10,He that fears God will pay heed
  87,11,but the wretched sinner will flout it
  87,12,He shall burn in the gigantic Fire
  87,13,wherein shall he then neither die nor live
  87,14,Happy shall be he that keeps himself pure
  87,15,that remembers the name of his Lord and prays
  87,16,Yet you¹ prefer the life of this world
  87,17,although the life to come is better and more lasting
  87,18,This is surely set down in earlier Scriptures
  87,19,the Scriptures of Abraham and Moses
  88,1,HAVE YOU heard of the Event that shall overwhelm all
  88,2,On that day there shall be downcast faces
  88,3,haggard and worn out
  88,4,burnt by a scorching fire
  88,5,drinking from a seething fountain
  88,6,Their only food shall be bitter thorns
  88,7,which will neither sustain them nor satisfy their hunger
  88,8,On that day there shall be radiant faces
  88,9,well-pleased with their labours
  88,10,in a lofty Garden
  88,11,Therein shall they hear no idle talk
  88,12,therein shall be a gushing fountain
  88,13,therein shall be raised soft couches
  88,14,with goblets placed before them
  88,15,silken cushions ranged in order
  88,16,and carpets richly spread
  88,17,"Do they never reflect on the camels, how they were created"
  88,18,"On the heaven, how it was raised on high"
  88,19,"On the mountains, how they were set down"
  88,20,"On the earth, how it was flattened"
  88,21,Therefore admonish; Your duty is only to admonish
  88,22,you are not their keeper
  88,23,As for those that turn their backs and disbelieve
  88,24,God will torment them with the supreme torment
  88,25,To Us shall they return
  88,26,and then We will Ourselves bring them to account
  89,1,BY THE Dawn
  89,2,and the Ten Nights¹
  89,3,"by that which is dual, and that which is single"
  89,4,"by the night, as it journeys on"
  89,5,Is there not in this a mighty oath for a man of sense
  89,6,Have you not considered how your Lord dealt with ‘Ād
  89,7,The many-columned city of Iram
  89,8,whose like has never been created in the land
  89,9,"And Thamūd, who hewed out their dwellings among the rocks of the valley"
  89,10,"And Pharaoh, who impaled his victims upon the stake"
  89,11,They had all led sinful lives
  89,12,and made the land teem with wickedness
  89,13,Therefore your Lord let loose on them the scourge of a torment
  89,14,for from His eminence your Lord observes all
  89,15,"As for man, when his Lord tests him by honouring him and bestowing blessings on him, he says: ‘My Lord has honoured me.‘"
  89,16,"But when He tests him by diminishing his provisions, he says: ‘My Lord despises me.‘"
  89,17,No! But you show no kindness to the orphan
  89,18,nor do you vie with each other in feeding the destitute
  89,19,Greedily you lay your hands on the inheritance of the weak
  89,20,and you love riches with all your hearts
  89,21,No! But when the earth is crushed to fine dust
  89,22,"and your Lord comes down with the angels, in their ranks"
  89,23,and Hell is on that day brought near ― on that day man will remember. And what will remembrance avail him
  89,24,"He will say: ‘Would that I had been charitable in my lifetime!‘"
  89,25,But on that day none will punish as He will punish
  89,26,and none will bind with chains like His
  89,27,O serene soul
  89,28,"Return to your Lord, well pleased, and pleasing in His sight"
  89,29,Join My servants
  89,30,and enter My Paradise
  90,1,I SWEAR by this city
  90,2,and you¹ are a resident of this city
  90,3,by the begetter² and all whom he begot
  90,4,We created man to try him with affliction
  90,5,Does he think that none has power over him
  90,6,I have squandered vast riches!‘ he says
  90,7,Does he think that none observed him
  90,8,Have We not given him two eyes
  90,9,"a tongue, and two lips"
  90,10,and shown him the two paths
  90,11,Yet he would not scale the Height
  90,12,Would that you knew what the Height is
  90,13,It is the freeing of a slave
  90,14,"the feeding, in the day of famine"
  90,15,of an orphaned relation
  90,16,or a needy man in distress
  90,17,to have faith and to enjoin fortitude and mercy
  90,18,Such are those that shall stand on the right hand
  90,19,but those that deny Our revelations shall stand on the left
  90,20,with a Fire close above them
  91,1,BY THE sun and his midday brightness
  91,2,"by the moon, when she rises after him"
  91,3,"by the day, when it reveals his splendour"
  91,4,"by the night, when it veils him"
  91,5,By the heaven and Him that built it
  91,6,by the earth and Him that spread it
  91,7,by the soul and Him that moulded it and inspired it
  91,8,with knowledge of sin and piety
  91,9,blessed shall be he that has kept it pure
  91,10,and ruined he that has corrupted it
  91,11,In its presumptuous pride Thamūd denied their apostle
  91,12,when its arch-sinner rose against him
  91,13,"God‘s apostle said: ‘This is God‘s own she-camel. Let her drink.‘"
  91,14,"They disbelieved him, and hamstrung her. And for their sin their Lord let loose His scourge upon them and razed their city to the ground"
  91,15,He did not fear the consequences
  92,1,"BY THE night, when she lets fall her darkness"
  92,2,and by the radiant day
  92,3,By Him that created the male and the female
  92,4,your endeavours have varied ends
  92,5,For him that gives and fears God
  92,6,and believes in goodness
  92,7,We shall smooth the path of salvation
  92,8,but for him that gives nothing and strives to enrich himself
  92,9,and disbelieves in goodness
  92,10,We shall smooth the path of affliction
  92,11,"When he breathes his last, his riches will not avail him"
  92,12,It is for Us to give guidance
  92,13,"Ours is the life to come, Ours the life of this world"
  92,14,"I warn you, then, of a blazing Fire"
  92,15,in which none shall burn save the hardened sinner
  92,16,who disbelieves and turns away
  92,17,But the good man who keeps himself pure by almsgiving shall keep away from it
  92,18,and so shall he that does good works
  92,19,"for the sake of his Lord the Most High only, seeking no recompense"
  92,20,"But only seeking the countenance of his Lord, Most High"
  92,21,He will surely be well pleased
  93,1,BY THE light of day
  93,2,and by the night when she spreads her darkness
  93,3,"your Lord has not forsaken you,¹ nor does He abhor you"
  93,4,The life to come holds a richer prize for you than this present life
  93,5,and you shall be gratified with what your Lord will give you
  93,6,Did He not find you an orphan and give you shelter
  93,7,And did He not find you in error and guide you
  93,8,And did He not find you poor and enrich you
  93,9,Therefore do not wrong the orphan
  93,10,nor chide away the beggar
  93,11,But proclaim the goodness of your Lord
  94,1,HAVE WE not lifted up your heart
  94,2,and relieved you¹ of the burden
  94,3,which weighed down your back
  94,4,And have We not given you high renown
  94,5,With every hardship there comes ease
  94,6,With every hardship there comes ease
  94,7,When your prayers are ended resume your toil
  94,8,and seek your Lord with all fervour
  95,1,"BY THE Fig, and by the Olive"
  95,2,By Mount Sinai
  95,3,and by this inviolate city.²
  95,4,We created man in a most noble image
  95,5,and then We shall reduce him to the lowest of the low
  95,6,"except those who believe and do good works, for theirs shall be a boundless recompense"
  95,7,What then after this can make you deny the Last Judgement
  95,8,Is God not the most just of judges
  96,1,READ IN the name of your Lord who created ―
  96,2,created Man from clots of blood
  96,3,Read! Your Lord is the Most Bountiful One
  96,4,who by the pen taught
  96,5,Man what he did not know
  96,6,No! Man transgresses
  96,7,"in thinking himself his own master:²"
  96,8,for to your Lord shall all return
  96,9,Consider the man who rebukes
  96,10,Our servant when he prays
  96,11,"Consider: does he follow the right guidance"
  96,12,or enjoin true piety
  96,13,"Do but consider: if he denies the Truth and pays no heed"
  96,14,does he not realize that God sees all
  96,15,"No! Let him desist, or We will drag him by the forelock"
  96,16,"his lying, sinful forelock"
  96,17,Then let him call his helpmates
  96,18,We will call the guards of Hell
  96,19,"No, never obey him! Prostrate yourself and come nearer"
  97,1,WE REVEALED it on the Night of Qadr.³
  97,2,Would that you knew what the Night of Qadr is like
  97,3,Better is the Night of Qadr than a thousand months
  97,4,On that night the angels and the Spirit by their Lord‘s leave come down with each command
  97,5,"Peace it is, till break of dawn"
  98,1,THE UNBELIEVERS among the People of the Book¹ and the pagans did not desist from unbelief until the Proof was given them
  98,2,an apostle from God reciting from purified pages
  98,3,infallible decrees
  98,4,Nor did those who were vouchsafed the Book divide themselves until the Proof was given them
  98,5,"Yet they were enjoined only to worship God and to consecrate their religion to Him, to attend to their prayers and to render the alms levy. That, surely, is the infallible faith"
  98,6,The unbelievers among the People of the Book and the pagans shall in the fire of Hell abide for ever. They are the vilest of all creatures
  98,7,But of all creatures those that believe and do good works are the noblest
  98,8,"Their recompense, in their Lord‘s presence, shall be the Gardens of Eden, watered by running brooks, wherein shall they abide for ever. God is well pleased with them, and they are well pleased with Him. Thus shall the God-fearing be rewarded"
  99,1,WHEN EARTH is rocked in her last convulsion
  99,2,when Earth shakes off her burdens
  99,3,"and Man says, ‘What may this mean?‘ ―"
  99,4,on that day she will proclaim her tidings
  99,5,for your Lord will have inspired her
  99,6,On that day mankind will come out in broken bands to be shown their labours
  99,7,Whoever did an atom‘s weight of good shall see it
  99,8,and whoever did an atom‘s weight of evil shall also see it
  100,1,BY THE snorting war steeds
  100,2,which strike fire with their hoofs
  100,3,as they gallop to the raid at morn
  100,4,and with a trail of dust
  100,5,cleave a massed army
  100,6,Man is ungrateful to his Lord
  100,7,To this he himself shall bear witness
  100,8,He loves riches with all his heart
  100,9,But is he not aware that when the dead are thrown out from their graves
  100,10,and their once hidden thoughts are laid bare
  100,11,their Lord will on that day have full knowledge of them all
  101,1,THE DISASTER
  101,2,What is the Disaster
  101,3,Would that you knew what the Disaster is
  101,4,On that day people shall become like scattered moths
  101,5,and the mountains like tufts of carded wool
  101,6,Then he whose good deeds weigh heavy in the scales
  101,7,shall live in bliss
  101,8,but he whose good deeds are light
  101,9,the Abyss shall be his home
  101,10,Would that you knew what this is like
  101,11,It is a scorching fire
  102,1,YOUR HEARTS are taken up with worldly gain
  102,2,from the cradle to the grave
  102,3,No! But you shall learn
  102,4,No! You then shall surely learn
  102,5,No! If you knew the Truth with certainty
  102,6,you would witness Hell
  102,7,you would then witness it with the certainty of your very eyes
  102,8,"Then, on that day, you shall surely be questioned about your bliss"
  103,1,I SWEAR by the declining day
  103,2,that perdition shall be the lot of Man
  103,3,except for those who believe and do good works; who exhort each other to justice and to fortitude
  104,1,WOE BETIDE every back-biting slanderer
  104,2,who amasses riches and sedulously hoards them
  104,3,thinking his wealth will render him immortal
  104,4,By no means! He shall be flung into the Destroying Flame
  104,5,Would that you knew what the Destroying Flame is like
  104,6,It is God‘s own kindled fire
  104,7,which will rise up to the hearts
  104,8,It will close in upon them
  104,9,in towering columns
  105,1,HAVE YOU not considered how your Lord dealt with the Army of the Elephant?¹
  105,2,Did He not confound their stratagem
  105,3,and send against them flocks of birds
  105,4,which pelted them with clay-stones
  105,5,so that they became like the withered stalks of plants which cattle had devoured
  106,1,FOR THE protection of Quraysh
  106,2,their protection in their winter and summer journeyings
  106,3,Therefore let them worship the Lord of this House
  106,4,who fed them when there was famine and shielded them from fear
  107,1,HAVE YOU considered him that denies the Last Judgement
  107,2,It is he who turns away the orphan
  107,3,and does not urge the feeding of the destitute
  107,4,Woe betide those who pray
  107,5,but are heedless of their prayer
  107,6,who make a show of piety
  107,7,and forbid alms-giving
  108,1,WE HAVE given you² abundance
  108,2,So pray to your Lord and sacrifice to Him
  108,3,He that hates you shall remain childless
  109,1,"SAY: ‘YOU blasphemers"
  109,2,I do not worship what you worship
  109,3,nor do you worship what I worship
  109,4,I shall never worship what you worship
  109,5,nor will you ever worship what I worship
  109,6,"You have your religion, and I have my religion.‘"
  110,1,WHEN GOD‘S help and victory come
  110,2,and you see people embrace God‘s Religion in multitudes
  110,3,give praise and glory to your Lord and seek His forgiveness. He is ever disposed to forgive
  111,1,MAY THE hands of Abu-Lahab² perish! And may he himself perish
  111,2,Nothing shall his wealth and gains avail him
  111,3,"He shall be burnt in a flaming fire,³"
  111,4,"and his wife, laden with firewood"
  111,5,shall have a rope of fibre round her neck
  112,1,"SAY: ‘GOD is One"
  112,2,the Eternal God
  112,3,"He begot none, nor was He begotten"
  112,4,And none is equal to Him.‘
  113,1,"SAY: ‘I seek refuge in the Lord of Daybreak"
  113,2,from the mischief of His creation
  113,3,from the mischief of the night when she spreads her darkness
  113,4,from the mischief of conjuring witches;¹
  113,5,"from the mischief of the envier, when he envies.‘"
  114,1,"SAY: ‘I seek refuge in the Lord of mankind"
  114,2,the King of mankind
  114,3,the God of mankind
  114,4,from the mischief of the slinking prompter
  114,5,who whispers in the hearts of mankind
  114,6,from jinn and mankind.‘